news.title: China takes steps to support some developers, boost demand in economy
news.para: Policymakers have been trying to stabilize the sector that accounts for a quarter of the national GDP after a string of defaults among developers and a slump in home sales.

news.title: Housing starts drop 9.6%, building permits fall 1.3% in US in July 2022
news.para: Housing starts plunged 9.6% to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 1.446 million units last month, the lowest level since February 2021.

news.title: Supertech twin towers: FIR against three former fire officers over NOC to illegal structures
news.para: The FIR has been lodged at the Phase 2 police station on the complaint of a current fire department official in the wake of an inquiry conducted by the Deputy Inspector General of Police, Fire Service Headquarters (Lucknow).

news.title: In two Chinese cities, civil servants told to help offload unsold homes
news.para: Sixian, a small city in the eastern province of Anhui, has required civil servants to sell property to their friends and family, the Chinese financial media outlet Yicai reported on Wednesday.

news.title: Signature Global posts Rs 115.5 crore net loss in FY22
news.para: Last month, the Delhi-based firm had filed the Draft Red Herring Prospectus (DRHP) with capital markets regulator Sebi to raise up to Rs 1,000 crore through an Initial Public Offering (IPO).

news.title: MahaREAT orders Satyam Developers to pay buyers Rs 25,000 for delaying possession
news.para: The direction was passed on an appeal by Satyam Developers against a February 2020 order of Maharashtra Real Estate Regulatory Authority (MahaRERA) to pay the allottee interest from January 1, 2018, till actual date of possession.

news.title: Nashik: Builders to be fined if mud from their sites makes roads slushy
news.para: Solid waste management (SWM) director Dr Avesh Palod said the NMC was forced to take such an action against the builders and developers as the situation often turned grim near the construction sites leading to accidents.

news.title: Large buildings to source 25% of energy need from green sources
news.para: The bill passed by Lok Sabha has now made it mandatory for the large residential buildings to use 25% of its energy consumption from renewable resources.

news.title: Tepid response to Swagruha flats' sale in Hyderabad
news.para: While about 3,900 flats were allotted to the applicants after they evinced interest in taking them last month, only 1,900 allottees have paid the amount.

news.title: Mumbai: Builder to pay Rs 20 lakh for labourer's death at site
news.para: The tribunal further said the money will have to be paid by the employer, Rameshwar Infra Partners, and not the insurance company.

news.title: Why razing Supertech twin towers is a tough job
news.para: But there is no blueprint on how to demolish a building. Every structure is unique, and with it, the challenges to raze it to the ground are distinct.

news.title: DDA plans 'mini draw' of lots for waitlisted applicants of housing scheme 2021 in Sept
news.para: In a public notice issued on Tuesday, the DDA said it is planning a "mini draw" of lots for waitlisted applicants of its Special Housing Scheme 2021 in September.

news.title: Residents of Supertech Ecovillage 2 threaten stir if work does not begin by Aug 28
news.para: Some of them have even decided to give their consent to Supertech, the developer, or NCLT-appointed interim resolution professional (IRP) to get the UP-Rera registration re-approved for the project, which might help in resuming the construction work.

news.title: South Korea to supply 2.7 million homes over five years
news.para: The government plans to supply 500,000 homes in the Seoul area over the five-year period, more than a 50% increase from the amount supplied over the past five years, the Ministry of Land, Infrastructure and Transport said in a statement.

news.title: Delhi Police arrests builder for duping homebuyers
news.para: According to the police, Gusain advertised for booking of flats and shops in the real estate project of his company, Asian Developers Pvt. Ltd, in Rewari in 2012.
